external.description: Here is a list of 20 reasons why Elon Musk's Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE)—the short-lived advisory initiative launched by President Trump in January 2025 to slash federal spending and bureaucracy—has been widely regarded as a terrible failure. Drawing from reports, analyses, and public reactions up to November 25, 2025, DOGE promised up to $2 trillion in cuts but delivered minimal verifiable savings, widespread disruption, and internal collapse, ultimately disbanding eight months early in July 2025 after Musk's exit.
